title: Fashion - From Ancient Egypt to the Present Day (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Fashion: From Ancient Egypt to the Present Day
The Odyssey Press | 1965 | ISBN: N/A | English | 326 pages | PDF | 74 MB


The history of fashion is the history of life. For fashion is far more than the wearing of clothes; the primitive caveman with his blue paint, the Cretan ladies who left their bosoms bare, the hair styles on Roman statues, the social life of the Renaissance courts, even the slim-hipped, boyish figures of twentieth century women, are but a few of the byproducts of fashion
